  (@custom "contractspecv0" (after data) "\00\00\00\04\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\0aVaultError\00\00\00\00\00\19\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\0cUnauthorized\00\00\00\01\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\0bVaultPaused\00\00\00\00\02\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\0dInvalidAmount\00\00\00\00\00\00\03\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\18SubaccountNotWhitelisted\00\00\00\04\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\1bSubaccountAlreadyRegistered\00\00\00\00\05\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\15AumChangeExceedsLimit\00\00\00\00\00\00\07\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\0cMathOverflow\00\00\00\08\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\15MaxSubaccountsReached\00\00\00\00\00\00\09\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\10InvalidAumLimits\00\00\00\0a\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\19SubaccountReturnedNothing\00\00\00\00\00\00\0b\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\17DeployedAssetsUnderflow\00\00\00\00\0c\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\0eNoPendingAdmin\00\00\00\00\00\0e\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\14InvalidAdminProposal\00\00\00\0f\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\14AdminProposalExpired\00\00\00\10\00\00\00=Strategy's configured asset does not match the vault's asset.\00\00\00\00\00\00\0dAssetMismatch\00\00\00\00\00\00\11\00\00\00Kdecimals_offset must be >= 3 to mitigate first-depositor inflation attacks.\00\00\00\00\15InvalidDecimalsOffset\00\00\00\00\00\00\12\00\00\007A strategy's `get_balance()` returned a negative value.\00\00\00\00\17NegativeStrategyBalance\00\00\00\00\13\00\00\00GCumulative AUM change within the current time window exceeds the limit.\00\00\00\00\1fAumCumulativeChangeExceedsLimit\00\00\00\00\14\00\00\01\13A strategy's `get_balance()` call failed (panicked, returned a non-i128,\0aor otherwise could not be invoked). The vault freezes total-assets-dependent\0aoperations until the admin removes the failing subaccount via\0a`remove_subaccount` (which does not make cross-contract calls).\00\00\00\00\13StrategyUnreachable\00\00\00\00\15\00\00\00\cfAn operation specific to `Wallet` subaccounts was invoked against a\0a`Strategy` subaccount (or vice versa). Distinct from `InvalidAmount`\0aso monitoring can tell a type-mismatch apart from a bad numeric input.\00\00\00\00\15InvalidSubaccountType\00\00\00\00\00\00\16\00\00\01O`withdraw_from_subaccount` attempted to pull more from a Wallet than\0athe per-wallet tracker records. Forces the operator to first reconcile\0athe wallet's attributed value via `update_wallet_deployed` (dust /\0again recognition) \e2\80\94 otherwise an over-pull would silently consume\0aanother wallet's share of `deployed_assets`, corrupting NAV.\00\00\00\00\12WalletOverWithdraw\00\00\00\00\00\17\00\00\03\8a`remove_subaccount` was called on a subaccount whose\0a`WalletNetDeployed` tracker is non-zero. Primary case (Wallet):\0aremoving without reconciliation would either strand value in\0a`deployed_assets` (if removed first) or open a pricing window\0abetween write-down and removal (if reconciled separately).\0aOperators must either drain the wallet to zero via\0a`withdraw_from_subaccount` or use `remove_wallet_and_reconcile`,\0awhich closes the window atomically under dual auth.\0a\0a**Defense-in-depth case (Strategy)**: the post-R2 guard is\0astate-based, not type-based \e2\80\94 it trips on any subaccount with a\0anon-zero tracker regardless of `SubaccountType`. A Strategy\0asubaccount never legitimately has a non-zero\0a`WalletNetDeployed`, so hitting this error on a Strategy\0aindicates storage corruption (stray tracker entry, wrong type\0astored). The fix in that case is to investigate the\0acorruption, not to drain-then-remove.\00\00\00\00\00\14WalletTrackerNotZero\00\00\00\18\00\00\01\c1`seed_wallet_net_deployed` was called with `amount < current_tracker`.\0aSeeding is an admin-only path that does not touch the aggregate\0a`deployed_assets`; allowing downward seeds would let an admin zero\0aa tracker to bypass `WalletTrackerNotZero` (#24) and then remove\0athe wallet, stranding value in the aggregate. Downward reconciliation\0amust go through `update_wallet_deployed` or\0a`remove_wallet_and_reconcile` (both move the aggregate in lockstep).\00\00\00\00\00\00\16WalletSeedBelowTracker\00\00\00\00\00\19\00\00\00\ec`update_wallet_deployed_batch` was called with an empty `updates`\0avector. Rejected for explicitness \e2\80\94 a no-op batch call is almost\0aalways a client-side bug (e.g. filtered list collapsed to empty)\0athat would otherwise silently succeed.\00\00\00\0aEmptyBatch\00\00\00\00\00\1a\00\00\01r`update_wallet_deployed_batch` was called with the same subaccount\0aaddress appearing more than once in `updates`. Rejected because\0athe net-delta computation would otherwise depend on iteration\0aorder (later pair overwrites earlier tracker value but the delta\0aapplied to the aggregate sums all pairs), breaking the atomic\0alockstep between per-wallet tracker and aggregate.\00\00\00\00\00\1aDuplicateSubaccountInBatch\00\00\00\00\00\1b\00\00\00\05\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\08AdminSet\00\00\00\01\00\00\00\09admin_set\00\00\00\00\00\00\01\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\05admin\00\00\00\00\00\00\13\00\00\00\01\00\00\00\02\00\00\00\05\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\0bOperatorSet\00\00\00\00\01\00\00\00\0coperator_set\00\00\00\03\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\05admin\00\00\00\00\00\00\13\00\00\00\01\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\0cold_operator\00\00\03\e8\00\00\00\13\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\0cnew_operator\00\00\00\13\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\02\00\00\00\05\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\0bVaultPaused\00\00\00\00\01\00\00\00\0cvault_paused\00\00\00\01\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\05admin\00\00\00\00\00\00\13\00\00\00\01\00\00\00\02\00\00\00\05\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\0dVaultUnpaused\00\00\00\00\00\00\01\00\00\00\0evault_unpaused\00\00\00\00\00\01\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\05admin\00\00\00\00\00\00\13\00\00\00\01\00\00\00\02\00\00\00\05\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\0fSubaccountAdded\00\00\00\00\01\00\00\00\10subaccount_added\00\00\00\03\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\05admin\00\00\00\00\00\00\13\00\00\00\01\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\0asubaccount\00\00\00\00\00\13\00\00\00\01\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\0fsubaccount_type\00\00\00\07\d0\00\00\00\0eSubaccountType\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\02\00\00\00\05\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\10AumLimitsChanged\00\00\00\01\00\00\00\12aum_limits_changed\00\00\00\00\00\05\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\05admin\00\00\00\00\00\00\13\00\00\00\01\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\10old_increase_bps\00\00\00\04\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\10old_decrease_bps\00\00\00\04\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\10new_increase_bps\00\00\00\04\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\10new_decrease_bps\00\00\00\04\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\02\00\00\00\05\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\11SubaccountRemoved\00\00\00\00\00\00\01\00\00\00\12subaccount_removed\00\00\00\00\00\05\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\05admin\00\00\00\00\00\00\13\00\00\00\01\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\0asubaccount\00\00\00\00\00\13\00\00\00\01\00\00\00\b7The vault-wide `deployed_assets` counter at the time of removal.\0aThis value is only meaningful for `Wallet`-type subaccounts;\0a`Strategy` balances are tracked live via `get_balance()`.\00\00\00\00\15total_deployed_assets\00\00\00\00\00\00\0b\00\00\00\00\00\00\02\1bFor `Strategy` subaccounts, the result of `try_get_balance()` at\0aremoval time: `Some(balance)` if the strategy responded with a\0avalid i128, `None` if the call trapped or returned an undecodable\0avalue (the vault still proceeds with removal to recover from a\0abroken strategy). Always `None` for `Wallet` subaccounts.\0a\0aThis is the on-chain record linking the share-price drop caused\0aby removing a funded strategy to the removal transaction itself \e2\80\94\0awithout it, off-chain auditors had no way to attribute the NAV\0achange to the removal event.\00\00\00\00\10strategy_balance\00\00\03\e8\00\00\00\0b\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\0fsubaccount_type\00\00\00\07\d0\00\00\00\0eSubaccountType\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\02\00\00\00\05\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\13DepositToSubaccount\00\00\00\00\01\00\00\00\15deposit_to_subaccount\00\00\00\00\00\00\04\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\08operator\00\00\00\13\00\00\00\01\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\0asubaccount\00\00\00\00\00\13