no divergence\22 for off-chain monitoring, so a silent skip of the\0a`WalletBalanceDiverged` diagnostic is still visible.\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\18WalletBalanceProbeFailed\00\00\00\01\00\00\00\1bwallet_balance_probe_failed\00\00\00\00\02\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\0asubaccount\00\00\00\00\00\13\00\00\00\01\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\14tracked_net_deployed\00\00\00\0b\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\02\00\00\00\05\00\00\03\e9Emitted from `do_remove_subaccount` when `try_get_balance` cannot\0aproduce an i128. Paired with `SubaccountRemoved`'s `strategy_balance:\0aNone` but carries the distinguishing reason code so auditors can\0adifferentiate the broken-strategy failure modes.\0a\0a**Off-chain correlation**: the two events are emitted in the same\0atransaction and share the `subaccount` topic. Indexers rebuilding\0athe full picture should correlate by `(tx_hash, subaccount)`:\0a- `SubaccountRemoved` alone with `strategy_balance = Some(n)` \e2\86\92\0aclean strategy removal, balance `n` exited NAV.\0a- `SubaccountRemoved` + `StrategyBalanceProbeFailed(InvokeError)` \e2\86\92\0astrategy was unreachable (trap, missing method, TTL expiry).\0a- `SubaccountRemoved` + `StrategyBalanceProbeFailed(ConvertError)` \e2\86\92\0astrategy responded but returned a non-i128; ABI regression.\0a- `SubaccountRemoved` alone with `strategy_balance = None` and\0a`subaccount_type = Wallet` \e2\86\92 wallet removal, not a strategy\0aprobe failure (the event is always `None` for wallets).\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\1aStrategyBalanceProbeFailed\00\00\00\00\00\01\00\00\00\1dstrategy_balance_probe_failed\00\00\00\00\00\00\02\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\0asubaccount\00\00\00\00\00\13\00\00\00\01\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\06reason\00\00\00\00\07\d0\00\00\00\14StrategyProbeFailure\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\02\00\00\00\05\00\00\04\00Emitted once per `update_wallet_deployed_batch` call to record that a\0agroup of per-wallet updates was applied as a single atomic unit.\0aIndexers use this as the transaction-level anchor for the N\0a`WalletDeployedUpdated` events that share the same transaction.\0a\0a`count` is the number of entries in the batch. `net_delta` is the net\0amove applied to `deployed_assets` \e2\80\94 equal to the sum of per-wallet\0adeltas. A zero `net_delta` is possible (e.g. one wallet gains 100k and\0aanother loses 100k in the same batch) and still emits this event as\0aan audit trail.\0a\0a**Emission order within the transaction** (indexers: scan backward\0afrom this event to collect the batch members):\0a\0a1. `DeployedAssetsChanged` \e2\80\94 once, from `apply_deployed_assets_change`.\0a2. `WalletDeployedUpdated` \e2\80\94 once per batch entry, in input order.\0a3. `WalletDeployedBatchApplied` \e2\80\94 this event, emitted last.\0a\0aThe anchor fires last rather than first so that all per-wallet events\0ait summarises have already been emitted when an indexer sees it; the\0acost is t\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\1aWalletDeployedBatchApplied\00\00\00\00\00\01\00\00\00\1dwallet_deployed_batch_applied\00\00\00\00\00\00\03\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\08operator\00\00\00\13\00\00\00\01\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\05count\00\00\00\00\00\00\04\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\09net_delta\00\00\00\00\00\00\0b\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\02\00\00\00\02\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\0aStorageKey\00\00\00\00\00\12\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\05Admin\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\08Operator\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\0eDeployedAssets\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\0bSubaccounts\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\10AumIncreaseLimit\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\10AumDecreaseLimit\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\06Paused\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\0fSubaccountTypes\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\0cPendingAdmin\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\13AdminProposalExpiry\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\11AumWindowDuration\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\1aAumCumulativeIncreaseLimit\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\1aAumCumulativeDecreaseLimit\00\00