window being opened by mistake.\0a\0aRemaining use cases for `remove_subaccount`:\0a- Strategy removal (balances tracked live via `get_balance()`).\0a- Wallet cleanup after a full pull via `withdraw_from_subaccount`\0ahas zeroed the tracker.\0a- Emergency decommissioning where the operator key is unavailable:\0athe admin must first rotate the operator (via\0a`set_operator`) and then go through `remove_wallet_and_reconcile`\0aor `update_wallet_deployed` to zero the\00\00\00\11remove_subaccount\00\00\00\00\00\00\02\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\05admin\00\00\00\00\00\00\13\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\0asubaccount\00\00\00\00\00\13\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\13get_deployed_assets\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\01\00\00\00\0b\00\00\00\00\00\00\01\0aReturns the type of a registered subaccount (`Strategy` or `Wallet`).\0a\0aPanics with `SubaccountNotWhitelisted` if the address is not in the\0acurrent whitelist. Defaults to `Strategy` for subaccounts registered\0abefore this field was introduced (backward compatibility).\00\00\00\00\00\13get_subaccount_type\00\00\00\00\01\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\0asubaccount\00\00\00\00\00\13\00\00\00\01\00\00\07\d0\00\00\00\0eSubaccountType\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00LCancel a pending admin transfer proposal. Only the current admin\0acan cancel.\00\00\00\15cancel_admin_proposal\00\00\00\00\00\00\01\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\05admin\00\00\00\00\00\00\13\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\02kTransfer `amount` of the underlying token from the vault to `subaccount`.\0a\0aFor `Strategy` subaccounts, notifies the strategy via `IStrategy::deposit`\0aafter the transfer. The strategy's balance is captured live by\0a`IStrategy::get_balance()` in `total_assets`, so `deployed_assets` is NOT\0aincremented. `Wallet` subaccounts receive the tokens directly with no\0afurther notification; their balance is not queried on-chain, so\0a`deployed_assets` IS incremented. No AUM rate limit is applied \e2\80\94\0asubaccount transfers don't change total_assets.\0a\0aRequires operator authorization, a non-paused vault, and a whitelisted\0asubaccount.\00\00\00\00\15deposit_to_subaccount\00\00\00\00\00\00\03\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\08operator\00\00\00\13\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\0asubaccount\00\00\00\00\00\13\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\06amount\00\00\00\00\00\0b\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\c3Sum of `IStrategy::get_balance()` across all Strategy-type subaccounts.\0aUseful for operators to see how much capital is visible on-chain in\0astrategies vs. the wallet-attributed `deployed_assets`.\00\00\00\00\15get_strategy_balances\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\01\00\00\00\0b\00\00\00\00\00\00\02\1cConfigure the cumulative AUM rate-limit window.\0a\0a`window_duration` \e2\80\94 length of the fixed window in seconds\0a(min 3,600 = 1 hour, max 604,800 = 7 days). The window resets\0aentirely on expiry (tumbling window, not sliding).\0a\0a`cumulative_increase_bps` / `cumulative_decrease_bps` \e2\80\94 maximum\0acumulative change (in basis points of the `base_deployed` snapshot\0ataken when the window resets) allowed within a single window.\0a\0aChanging limits resets the active window so the new configuration\0atakes effect immediately with a clean cumulative state.\00\00\00\15set_aum_window_limits\00\00\00\00\00\00\04\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\05admin\00\00\00\00\00\00\13\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\0fwindow_duration\00\00\00\00\06\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\17cumulative_increase_bps\00\00\00\00\04\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\17cumulative_decrease_bps\00\00\00\00\04\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\16get_aum_decrease_limit\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\01\00\00\00\04\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\16get_aum_increase_limit\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\01\00\00\00\04\00\00\00\00\00\00\04\00Aggregate-only emergency escape hatch for `deployed_assets`.\0a\0a**Deprecated for routine use** after F4: strategies self-report\0atheir full position (idle + deployed) via `IStrategy::get_balance()`,\0aso `deployed_assets` no longer has a legitimate \22strategy off-chain\0aAUM\22 component. The standard operator path for wallet-attributed\0areconciliation is `update_wallet_deployed` (single wallet) or\0a`update_wallet_deployed_batch` (multiple wallets atomically) \e2\80\94 both\0amove the per-wallet tracker and the aggregate in lockstep, so the\0ainvariant `\ce\a3 WalletNetDeployed == deployed_assets` is preserved.\0a\0aRemaining legitimate uses:\0a- Recovery from a storage anomaly where the invariant has already\0abroken and the aggregate needs a correction that cannot be\0aattributed to specific wallets.\0a- Temporary aggregate correction during a multi-step migration that\0awill restore the invariant in a follow-up transaction.\0a\0a**Warning**: this function can break the wallet-tracker sum\0ainvariant by design. Off-chain monitoring should compare\0a`get_\00\00\00\16update_deployed_assets\00\00\00\00\00\02\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\08operator\00\00\00\13\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\06amount\00\00\00\00\00\0b\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\03eReconcile a single Wallet subaccount's attributed value. Atomically\0amoves both the per-wallet tracker (to `new_tracked`) and the\0aaggregate `deployed_assets` counter (by the same delta), so\0asubsequent `withdraw_from_subaccount` calls can pull the full value\0awithout tripping the per-wallet over-pull check.\0a\0aUse cases:\0a- Recognising a gain (wallet appreciated): `new_tracked > current`.\0a- Recognising a loss (wallet depreciated): `new_tracked < current`.\0a- Recognising external dust the operator wants to recover:\0a`new_tracked = current + dust_amount`, then pull.\0a\0aSubject to the same AUM rate limits and pause semantics as\0a`update_deployed_assets`: increases are rejected while paused;\0adecreases remain allowed for loss recovery.\0a\0aFor aggregate-only reconciliation (e.g. strategy external AUM not\0aattributable to a specific wallet) use `update_deployed_assets`\0ainstead.\00\00\00\00\00\00\16update_wallet_deployed\00\00\00\00\00\03\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\08operator\00\00\00\13\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\0asubaccount\00\00\00\00\00\13\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\0bnew_tracked\00\00\00\00\0b\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00WLength of the cumulative AUM rate-limit window in seconds\0a(default: 86,400 = 24 hours).\00\00\00\00\17get_aum_window_duration\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\01\00\00\00\06\00\00\00\00\00\00\01\1dRead the per-wallet net-deployed tracker for a subaccount.\0a\0aReturns 0 for unregistered addresses, for Strategy subaccounts, and\0afor Wallet subaccounts that have never been deposited to. Useful for\0aadmins verifying the result of `seed_wallet_net_deployed` and for\0amonitoring dashboards.\00\00\00\00\00\00\17get_wallet_net_deployed\00\00\00\00\01\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\0asubaccount\00\00\00\00\00\13\00\00\00\01\00\00\00\0b\00\00\00\00\00\00\00UMaximum cumulative AUM decrease within a window, in basis points\0a(default: 500 = 5%).\00\00\00\00\00\00\18get_aum_window_dec_limit\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\01\00\00\00\04\00\00\00\00\00\00\00XMaximum cumulative AUM increase within a window, in basis points\0a(default: 1,000 = 10%).\00\00\00\18get_aum_window_inc_limit\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\01\00\00\00\04\00\00\00\00\00\00\04\00Per-wallet emergency escape hatch for the `WalletNetDeployed`\0atracker. **Restricted to emergency storage corrections** after F4:\0athe standard operator path for gain/loss recognition and dust\0aattribution is `update_wallet_deployed` (single wallet) or\0a`update_wallet_deployed_batch` (multiple wallets atomically),\0awhich move the per-wallet tracker and the aggregate\0a`deployed_assets` in lockstep and preserve the invariant\0a`\ce\a3 WalletNetDeployed == deployed_assets`.\0a\0aRemaining legitimate uses:\0a- Backfilling the tracker for a wallet registered before per-wallet\0aaccounting was introduced (one-shot upgrade migration).\0a- Correcting a divergence between `get_deployed_assets()` and\0a`get_wallet_deployed_assets()` after a storage anomaly or a prior\0a`update_deployed_assets` correction that left wallet attribution\0aout of sync.\0a\0a**Warning**: this function can break the wallet-tracker sum\0ainvariant by design. It does NOT touch the aggregate\0a`deployed_assets` \e2\80\94 use it only when the value being attributed is\0aalready recorded in\00\00\00\18seed_wallet_net_deployed\00\00\00\03\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\05admin\00\00\00\00\00\00\13\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\0asubaccount\00\00\00\00\00\13\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\06amount\00\00\00\00\00\0b\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\02\c8Request `amount` of the underlying token back from `subaccount`.\0a\0aFor `Strategy` subaccounts, calls `IStrategy::withdraw` (push model).\0aStrategy balances are queried live via `get_balance()`, so\0a`deployed_assets` is NOT decremented.\0a\0aFor `Wallet` subaccounts, pulls tokens via `transfer_from` using a\0apre-approved SEP-41 allowance. The wallet owner (EOA or contract) must\0ahave called `token.approve(wallet, vault, amount, ledger)` beforehand.\0a`deployed_assets` IS decremented for wallets.\0a\0aMeasures actual tokens received via balance-differencing. No AUM rate\0alimit is applied \e2\80\94 subaccount transfers don't change total_assets.\0a\0aRequires operator authorization, a non-paused vault, and a whitelisted\0asubaccount.\00\00\00\18withdraw_from_subaccount\00\00\00\03\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\08operator\00\00\00\13\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\0asubaccount\00\00\00\00\00\13\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\06amount\00\00\00\00\00\0b\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\02VSum of `WalletNetDeployed` across all Wallet-type subaccounts\0acurrently in the whitelist.\0a\0aExposes the \ce\a3 side of the F4 invariant\0a`\ce\a3 WalletNetDeployed == deployed_assets` for off-chain monitoring.\0aUnder normal operation this returns the same value as\0a`get_deployed_assets()`. Divergence indicates one of the\0adocumented escape hatches (`update_deployed_assets` or\0a`seed_wallet_net_deployed`) has been used; the gap represents\0aaggregate value not currently attributed to any wallet.\0a\0aBounded cost: the subaccount list is capped at `MAX_SUBACCOUNTS`\0a(= 10), so this iterates at most ten map lookups.\00\00\00\00\00\1aget_wallet_deployed_assets\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\01\00\00\00\0b\00\00\00\00\00\00\04\00Atomically reconcile the aggregate `deployed_assets` counter AND\0aremove a Wallet subaccount in a single transaction.\0a\0aCloses the pricing window between the two-step sequence:\0a1. `update_deployed_assets(operator, new_total)`\0a2. `remove_subaccount(admin, wallet)`\0a\0aBetween those transactions NAV is wrong in one direction or the\0aother (write-down first: NAV under-reports while tokens still sit\0aat the wallet \e2\86\92 deposits mint too many shares; remove first: NAV\0aover-reports against stranded value \e2\86\92 redeems overpay). Combining\0aboth into one call eliminates the window.\0a\0aRequires both `admin` (whitelist authority) and `operator` (AUM\0aauthority) to authorise \e2\80\94 the combined function unions their\0apermissions without granting either role unilateral access to the\0aother's powers. When a single entity holds both keys (documented\0asupported configuration on `set_operator`), the operator's\0a`require_auth` is skipped to avoid Soroban's `Auth, ExistingValue`\0aerror that otherwise fires on a repeated auth of the same address.\0aSu\00\00\00\1bremove_wallet_and_reconcile\00\00\00\00\04\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\05admin\00\00\00\00\00\00\13\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\08operator\00\00\00\13\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\0asubaccount\00\00\00\00\00\13\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\12new_deployed_total\00\00\00\00\00\0b\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\04\00Reconcile multiple Wallet subaccounts atomically in a single call.\0aIntroduced as the F4 primary operator path for wallet-attributed\0areconciliation: replaces ad-hoc sequences of `update_wallet_deployed`\0acalls with one transaction that moves the aggregate exactly once\0a(so the AUM rate limit is applied to the net delta rather than to\0aeach intermediate step).\0a\0aEach `(subaccount, new_tracked)` entry is validated independently\0a(whitelisted, Wallet type, non-negative tracker). The net delta\0a`\ce\a3(new_tracked - old_tracked)` is applied to `deployed_assets` via\0athe shared `apply_deployed_assets_change` helper, so the AUM rate\0alimit is measured against the net (a batch with +100k on wallet A\0aand -100k on wallet B passes even when each individual step would\0aexceed the limit). Pause is enforced **per entry**: while paused,\0aany positive entry delta panics with `VaultPaused` regardless of\0athe batch's net \e2\80\94 this matches `update_wallet_deployed` (where\0aper-entry and net deltas coincide) and prevents a paused vault\0afrom accep\00\00\00\1cupdate_wallet_deployed_batch\00\00\00\02\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\08operator\00\00\00\13\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\07updates\00\00\00\03\ea\00\00\03\ed\00\00\00\02\00\00\00\13\00\00\00\0b\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\04\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\10UpgradeableError\00\00\00\01\00\00\00AWhen migration is attempted but not allowed due to upgrade state.\00\00\00\00\00\00\13MigrationNotAllowed\00\00\00\04L\00\00\00\02\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\15UpgradeableStorageKey\00\00\00\00\00\00\01\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\09Migrating\00\00\00\00\00\00\05\00\00\00*Event emitted when the merkle root is set.\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\07SetRoot\00\00\00\00\01\00\00\00\08set_root\00\00\00\01\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\04root\00\00\00\0e\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\02\00\00\00\05\00\00\00'Event emitted when an index is claimed.\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\0aSetClaimed\00\00\00\00\00\01\00\00\00\0bset_claimed\00\00\00\00\01\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\05index\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\02\00\00\00\04\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\16MerkleDistributorError\00\00\00\00\00\03\00\00\00\1bThe merkle root is not set.\00\00\00\00\0aRootNotSet\00\00\00\00\05\14\00\00\00'The provided index was already claimed.\00\00\00\00\13IndexAlreadyClaimed\00\00\00\05\15\00\00\00\15The proof is invalid.\00\00\00\00\00\00\0cInvalidProof\00\00\05\16\00\00\00\02\00\00\00=Storage keys for the data associated with `MerkleDistributor`\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\1bMerkleDistributorStorageKey\00\00\00\00\02\00\00\00\00\00\00\00(The Merkle root of the distribution tree\00\00\00\04Root\00\00\00\01\00\00\00#Maps an index to its claimed status\00\00\00\00\07Claimed\00\00\00\00\01\00\00\00\04\00\00\00\02\00\00\00*Rounding direction for division operations\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\08Rounding\00\00\00\03\00\00\00\00\00\00\00%Round toward negative infinity (down)\00\00\00\00\00\00\05Floor\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00#Round toward positive infinity (up)\00\00\00\00\04Ceil\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\1eRound toward zero (truncation)\00\00\00\00\00\08Truncate\00\00\00\04\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\16SorobanFixedPointError\00\00\00\00\00\02\00\00\00\1cArithmetic overflow occurred\00\00\00\08Overflow\00\00\05\dc\00\00\00\10Division by zero\00\00\00\0eDivisionByZero\00\00\00\00\05\dd\00\00\00\04\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\0bCryptoError\00\00\00\00\03\00\00\00)The merkle proof length is out of bounds.\00\00\00\00\00\00\16MerkleProofOutOfBounds\00\00\00\00\05x\00\00\00'The index of the leaf is out of bounds.\00\00\00\00\16MerkleIndexOutOfBounds\00\00\00\00\05y\00\00\00\18No data in hasher state.\00\00\00\10HasherEmptyState\00\00\05z\00\00\00\05\00\00\00*Event emitted when the contract is paused.\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\06Paused\00\00\00\00\00\01\00\00\00\06paused\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\02\00\00\00\05\00\00\00,Event emitted when the contract is unpaused.\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\08Unpaused\00\00\00\01\00\00\00\08unpaused\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\02\00\00\00\04\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\0dPausableError\00\00\00\00\00\00\02\00\00\004The operation failed because the contract is paused.\00\00\00\0dEnforcedPause\00\00\00\00\00\03\e8\00\00\008The operation failed because the contract is not paused.\00\00\00\0dExpectedPause\00\00\00\00\00\03\e9\00\00\00\02\00\00\00\22Storage key for the pausable state\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\00\12PausableStorageKey\00\00\00\00\00\01\00\00\00\00\00\00\002Indicate